    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-10T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-10T09:00:00-05:00" n="665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/5960: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-10T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 10, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>124. General Weygand<note n="70" xml:id="d665fn70">Gen. Maxime Weygand, formerly
                        Minister of National Defense in Marshal Pétain’s Cabinet.</note> arrived
                    yesterday afternoon to establish headquarters here with a small staff and the
                    title “Delegate General of the (Vichy) Government in French Africa” for the
                    briefly announced purpose of assuring the protection of the French African bloc
                    and furthering its economic prosperity by coordinating the administrative and
                    political action of the Residents and Governors General.</p>
                <p>The habitually un-city [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] population received him with
                    unusual apathy and the atmosphere at the official reception was strained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
